    "text": "I implemented a minimal GCC GIMPLE optimization pass that counts basic blocks per function in /workspace/gimple-count-bbs.cc. The implementation follows established GCC patterns from the following source files:\n\n## Key Reference Files\n\n### gcc/tree-pass.h\nDefines the core infrastructure:\n- `struct pass_data` \u2014 metadata struct with fields: type (opt_pass_type enum), name (const char*), optinfo_flags, tv_id, properties_required, properties_provided, properties_destroyed, todo_flags_start, todo_flags_finish\n- `class gimple_opt_pass : public opt_pass` \u2014 base class for all GIMPLE passes, with protected constructor taking `const pass_data&` and `gcc::context*`\n- `class opt_pass` \u2014 base class with virtual `gate(function*)` and `execute(function*)` methods\n- `GIMPLE_PASS` enum value for pass type\n- `PROP_cfg`, `PROP_ssa` property flags\n- `OPTGROUP_NONE`, `TV_NONE` constants\n\n### gcc/tree-ssa-dce.cc\nThe primary reference for the pass pattern:\n- Defines `const pass_data pass_data_dce` with GIMPLE_PASS type\n- `class pass_dce_base : public gimple_opt_pass` with `gate()` returning `flag_tree_dce != 0`\n- `class pass_dce : public pass_dce_base` with `execute()` method\n- `make_pass_dce(gcc::context*)` factory function returning `new pass_dce(ctxt)`\n- Uses `if (dump_file) fprintf(dump_file, ...)` pattern for debug output\n\n### gcc/adjust-alignment.cc\nSimplest complete pass example:\n- `const pass_data pass_data_adjust_alignment` with TV_NONE, no properties required\n- `class pass_adjust_alignment : public gimple_opt_pass` with only `execute()` override\n- `make_pass_adjust_alignment(gcc::context*)` factory\n- No `gate()` override (defaults to always-true)\n\n### gcc/gimple-laddress.cc\nDemonstrates `FOR_EACH_BB_FN` macro usage:\n- `FOR_EACH_BB_FN (bb, fun)` to iterate all basic blocks in a function\n- `gate()` returning `optimize != 0`\n- `clone()` returning `new pass_laddress(m_ctxt)`\n- Requires `PROP_cfg | PROP_ssa`\n\n### gcc/profile.cc\nDemonstrates `n_basic_blocks_for_fn` and dump_file usage:\n- `n_basic_blocks_for_fn(cfun)` to get the basic block count\n- `fprintf(dump_file, \"%d basic blocks\\n\", n_basic_blocks_for_fn(cfun))` pattern\n\n### gcc/function.h\n- `function_name(const function*)` \u2014 returns the name of a function for display\n- `n_basic_blocks_for_fn` macro/function\n- `cfun` global pointer to current function\n\n## Implementation Summary\n\nThe pass `pass_count_bbs` in `/workspace/gimple-count-bbs.cc`:\n1. Defines `const pass_data pass_data_count_bbs` with `GIMPLE_PASS` type, name `\"count_bbs\"`, `PROP_cfg` required\n2. Defines `class pass_count_bbs : public gimple_opt_pass` inside an anonymous namespace\n3. Implements `gate(function*)` returning `true` (always run)\n4. Implements `execute(function*)` using `FOR_EACH_BB_FN` to count basic blocks, then reports via `dump_file` using `fprintf(dump_file, \"Function %s: %d basic blocks...\")`\n5. Provides `make_pass_count_bbs(gcc::context*)` factory function outside the anonymous namespace\n\nThe includes follow the pattern from `gcc/gimple-ssa-nonnull-compare.cc`: config.h, system.h, coretypes.h, backend.h, tree.h, gimple.h, tree-pass.h, plus function.h, basic-block.h, cfg.h for the CFG iteration APIs. Note that `dumpfile.h` is already included transitively via `tree-pass.h` (line 26 of tree-pass.h)."
